main event: Unidentified radar targets were sighted by the Commanding Officer of the 1954 AACS Squadron at Misawa AFB, Japan on 10 February 1953.
interesting points: The radar operators reported unidentified interference on their radar scope., A F-94 aircraft was scrambled in response to the radar targets., The unidentified objects were plotted on the GCA scope., The radar returns indicated movement at approximately 50 knots., No visual confirmation of the objects was made by the aircraft.
witness description: radar operators from the 1954 AACS Squadron
